    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="781"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files: Lot F–96, Box 2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        Chairman of the Council of Peopled Commissars of the Soviet Union</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stalin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="34" xml:id="d781fn1">Paraphrase received through Naval
                        channels at the Embassy in Moscow on April 3, 1944, and sent on for Stalin
                        in a letter to Molotov on the next day.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1944-04-04">April 4, 1944</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>Many thanks for your message of March 25.<note n="35" xml:id="d781fn2">For text,
                        see Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the U.S.S.R.: <hi rend="italic"
                            >Correspondence Between the Chairman of the Council of Ministers of the
                            U.S.S.R. and the Presidents of the U.S.A. and the Prime Ministers of
                            Great Britain During the Great Patriotic War of 1941–1945</hi>, vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 136.</note> It is my hope that the
                    International Labor Organization at the coming meeting will <pb facs="0867"
                        n="857" xml:id="pg_857"/> make it clear that it no longer is an organ of the
                    League of Nations and that it will affiliate itself with the United Nations. I
                    trust, therefore, that the Soviet Union will have representatives at the next
                    conference.</p>
                <p>I will keep you informed of what takes place at the meeting in Philadelphia.</p>
            </div>
